## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-102">Eine Instanz von <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs> wird erstellt, wenn <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> das-Objekt <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> das-Ereignis auslöst.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> object raises the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-103">Das <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> löst dieses Ereignis für jedes neue Wort aus, das in einer Eingabeaufforderung mit einer <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.Speak%2A>der Methoden <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakAsync%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakSsml%2A>, oder <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakSsmlAsync%2A> verwendet wird.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-103">The <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> raises this event for each new word that it speaks in a prompt using any of the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.Speak%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakAsync%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakSsml%2A>, or <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakSsmlAsync%2A> methods.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-104">Die zurückgegebenen Daten basieren auf der Sprachsynthese Markup Language (SSML), die vom Code generiert wird.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-104">The returned data is based on the Speech Synthesis Markup Language (SSML) that the code generates.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-105">Die für <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterCount%2A> zurückgegebenen Werte enthalten Leerzeichen und die Zeichen und Inhalte der vom Code generierten SSML-Tags.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-105">The values returned for <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterCount%2A> include spaces and the characters and contents of the SSML tags generated by the code.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-106">Im folgenden Beispiel werden die Informationen veranschaulicht, die in <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs>verfügbar sind.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-106">The following example demonstrates the information that is available from <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-107">Beachten Sie, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.StartParagraph%2A>wie <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.EndParagraph%2A>sich <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.StartSentence%2A>die Methoden <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.EndSentence%2A> ,, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterCount%2A>  **undauf\<** den auswirken, indem Sie **p >,/p >, s > hinzufügen. \<**  **\<** /s > der generierten SSML-Tags.  **\<**</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-107">Note how the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.StartParagraph%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.EndParagraph%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.StartSentence%2A>, and <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.EndSentence%2A> methods affect the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterCount%2A> by their addition of **\<p>**, **\</p>**, **\<s>**, and **\</s>** tags to the generated SSML.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-108">Außerdem gibt es zwei Einträge in der Ausgabe für "30%", eine für jedes Wort, um diese Zahlen Zeichenfolge (dreißig Prozent) zu sprechen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-108">Also, there are two entries in the output for "30%", one for each word to speak this number string (thirty percent).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-109"><xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterCount%2A> Und<xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> sind für jeden Eintrag identisch und stellen die Zeichen "30%" dar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-109">The <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterCount%2A> and <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> are the same for each entry and represent the characters "30%.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-110">Die <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> Änderungen an entsprechen jedoch der Sprache "dreißig" und "Prozent" <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer>von.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-110">However, the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> changes to reflect the speaking of the words "thirty" and "percent" by the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Synthesis;  
  
namespace SampleSynthesis  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
  
      // Initialize a new instance of the SpeechSynthesizer.  
      using (SpeechSynthesizer synth = new SpeechSynthesizer())  
      {  
  
        // Configure the audio output.   
        synth.SetOutputToWaveFile(@"C:\test\weather.wav");  
  
        // Create a SoundPlayer instance to play the output audio file.  
        System.Media.SoundPlayer m_SoundPlayer =  
          new System.Media.SoundPlayer(@"C:\test\weather.wav");  
  
        // Build a prompt containing a paragraph and two sentences.  
        PromptBuilder builder = new PromptBuilder(  
          new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US"));  
        builder.StartParagraph();  
        builder.StartSentence();  
        builder.AppendText(  
          "The weather forecast for today is partly cloudy with some sun breaks.");  
        builder.EndSentence();  
        builder.StartSentence();  
        builder.AppendText(  
          "Tonight's weather will be cloudy with a 30% chance of showers.");  
        builder.EndSentence();  
        builder.EndParagraph();  
  
        // Add a handler for the SpeakProgress event.  
        synth.SpeakProgress +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeakProgressEventArgs>(synth_SpeakProgress);  
  
        // Speak the prompt and play back the output file.  
        synth.Speak(builder);  
        m_SoundPlayer.Play();  
      }  
  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Press any key to exit...");  
      Console.ReadKey();  
    }  
  
    // Write each word and its character position to the console.  
    static void synth_SpeakProgress(object sender, SpeakProgressEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("CharPos: {0}   CharCount: {1}   AudioPos: {2}    \"{3}\"",  
        e.CharacterPosition, e.CharacterCount, e.AudioPosition, e.Text);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-125"><xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> Enthält die Anzahl der Zeichen in XML-Tags, einschließlich ihrer einschließenden Klammern.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-125">The <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> includes the count for characters in XML tags, including their enclosing brackets.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-126">Wenn Sie <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendText%2A>eine der Methoden, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendTextWithAlias%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendTextWithHint%2A> <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendSsmlMarkup%2A>, oder <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendTextWithPronunciation%2A> verwenden, werden die Inhalte zu einer SSML-Eingabeaufforderung hinzugefügt, die die öffnenden und Schließ `speak` enden Elemente enthält.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-126">When using any of the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendText%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendTextWithAlias%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendTextWithHint%2A>, <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendSsmlMarkup%2A>, or <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendTextWithPronunciation%2A> methods, the contents are added to an SSML prompt that includes the opening and closing `speak` elements.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-127">Das öffnende `speak` Element fügt der <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> der Eingabeaufforderung einen Offset von 82 Zeichen und Leerzeichen hinzu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-127">The opening `speak` element adds an offset of 82 characters and spaces to the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> of the all the words and letters in the prompt.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-128">Im folgenden Code Ausschnitt ist beispielsweise der <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> des ersten Worts "This" 82.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-128">For example, in the following snippet, the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> of the first word, "this", is 82.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
builder.AppendText("This is a test");  
Synthesizer.Speak(builder);  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-129">Im obigen Beispiel <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> ist 92 der Begriff "Test".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-129">In the above example the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> of the word "test" is 92.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-130">Im folgenden Code Ausschnitt ist das <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> Wort "Test" 23 Zeichen höher (115), da die öffnende  **\<prosody-Tonhöhe = "High" >** -Tags, das dieser vorangestellt ist, 23 Zeichen und Leerzeichen enthält (\\ die beiden Escapezeichen " "werden nicht gezählt."</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-130">In the following snippet the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> of the word "test" is 23 characters higher (115) because the opening **\<prosody pitch="high">**  tag that precedes it contains 23 characters and spaces (the two escape characters "\\" are not counted).</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
builder.AppendSsmlMarkup("This is a <prosody pitch=\"high\"> test </prosody>.");   
Synthesizer.Speak(builder);  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-131">Wenn Sie die <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendSsml%2A> -Methoden verwenden, um einer Eingabeaufforderung Inhalt hinzuzufügen, indem Sie eine Datei angeben `speak` , werden die öffnende `xml` Deklaration und die Elemente in der Datei nicht verwendet oder gezählt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-131">If you use the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder.AppendSsml%2A> methods to add content to a prompt by specifying a file, the opening `xml` declaration and `speak` elements in the file are not used or counted.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-132">Das erste Zeichen in der Datei nach dem öffnenden `speak` Tag wird an Position 82 angezeigt, wenn es sich um den ersten Inhalt der Eingabeaufforderung handelt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-132">The first character in the file after the opening `speak` tag will be at position 82 if it is the first content in the prompt.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-133">Im Gegensatz dazu wird der Zeichen folgen Parameter <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.Speak%2A> einer Methode vor dem sprechen nicht zu einer SSML-Eingabeaufforderung hinzugefügt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-133">By contrast, the string parameter of a <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.Speak%2A> method does not get added to an SSML prompt before being spoken.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-134">Daher ist der <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> des ersten Worts "This" im folgenden Code Ausschnitt 0 (null).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-134">Therefore, the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> of the first word, "this", in the following snippet is zero.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
Synthesizer.Speak("This is a test.");  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-135">Der <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> normalisiert Zahlen in die Wörter, die der Art und Weise entsprechen, in der die Zahl gesprochen wird.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-135">The <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> normalizes numbers to the words that correspond to how the number will be spoken.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-136">Der Synthesizer spricht z. b. die Zahl "4003" als "4003".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-136">For example, the synthesizer speaks the number "4003" as "four thousand three".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-137">Es löst ein <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> -Ereignis für jedes der drei gesprochenen Wörter aus.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-137">It raises a <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> event for each of the three spoken words.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-138">Allerdings ist <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> die-Eigenschaft für jedes der drei Wörter identisch.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-138">However, the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> property for each of the three words is the same.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-139">Dies ist die Position vor dem ersten Zeichen der Zahl "4003" im Text der Eingabeaufforderung.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-139">It is the position before the first character of the number "4003" in the text of the prompt.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-140">Im folgenden Beispiel wird eine <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder> erstellt, die den SSML-Inhalt einer XML-Datei <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>mithilfe von anfügt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-140">The following example creates a <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.PromptBuilder> and appends the SSML contents of an XML file using <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-141">Im Beispiel wird die Sprache für die Wiedergabe in eine WAV-Datei ausgegeben.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-141">The example outputs speech to a WAV file for playback.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-142">Der Inhalt der XML-Datei, die SSML enthält, wird unterhalb des Code Beispiels angezeigt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-142">The contents of the XML file containing the SSML appear below the code example.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System;  
using System.Xml;  
using System.IO;  
using System.Speech.Synthesis;  
  
namespace SampleSynthesis  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
  
      // Initialize a new instance of the SpeechSynthesizer.  
      using (SpeechSynthesizer synth = new SpeechSynthesizer())  
      {  
  
        // Configure the audio output.   
        synth.SetOutputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Create a path to the file that contains SSML.  
        string weatherFile = Path.GetFullPath("c:\\test\\Weather.ssml");  
  
        // Create an XML Reader from the file, create a PromptBuilder and   
        // append the XmlReader.  
        PromptBuilder builder = new PromptBuilder();  
  
        if (File.Exists(weatherFile))  
        {  
          XmlReader reader = XmlReader.Create(weatherFile);  
          builder.AppendSsml(reader);  
          reader.Close();  
        }  
  
        // Add a handler for the SpeakProgress event.  
        synth.SpeakProgress +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeakProgressEventArgs>(synth_SpeakProgress);  
  
        // Speak the prompt and play back the output file.  
        synth.Speak(builder);  
      }  
  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Press any key to exit...");  
      Console.ReadKey();  
    }  
  
    // Write each word and its character position to the console.  
    static void synth_SpeakProgress(object sender, SpeakProgressEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speak progress: {0} {1}",  
        e.CharacterPosition, e.Text);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```  
  
```xml  
<!-- The following are the contents of the file Weather.ssml.   
Note that because of the <p> tag and the space that follows it,   
that the character position of the first word "The" will be 86. -->  
  
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1"?>  
<speak version="1.0"  
 xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/10/synthesis"  
 xml:lang="en-US">  
  
  <p> The weather forecast for today is partly cloudy with   
some sun breaks. </p>  
  
  <break strength="medium" />  
  
  <p> Tonight's weather will be cloudy with a 30% chance of   
showers. </p>  
  
</speak>  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-145">Der <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> normalisiert Zahlen in die Wörter, die der Art und Weise entsprechen, in der die Zahl gesprochen wird.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-145">The <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer> normalizes numbers to the words that correspond to how the number will be spoken.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-146">Der Synthesizer spricht z. b. die Zahl "4003" als "4003".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-146">For example, the synthesizer speaks the number "4003" as "four thousand three".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-147">Es löst ein <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> -Ereignis für jedes der gesprochenen Wörter aus.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-147">It raises a <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> event for each of the spoken words.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-148">Allerdings ist <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.Text%2A> die-Eigenschaft für jedes der drei Wörter identisch.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-148">However, the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.Text%2A> property for each of the three words is the same.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-149">Dabei handelt es sich um den Text "4003" von der Eingabeaufforderung.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-149">It is the text "4003" from the prompt.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b0c6e-150">Im folgenden Beispiel wird veranschaulicht, wie <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> das-Ereignis <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> die <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.Text%2A> -Eigenschaft und die-Eigenschaft für Zeichen folgen mit Zahlen meldet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b0c6e-150">The following example illustrates the how the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer.SpeakProgress> event reports the <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.CharacterPosition%2A> and <xref:System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeakProgressEventArgs.Text%2A> properties for strings that contain numbers.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System;  
using System.Xml;  
using System.IO;  
using System.Speech.Synthesis;  
  
namespace SampleSynthesis  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
  
      // Initialize a new instance of the SpeechSynthesizer.  
      using (SpeechSynthesizer synth = new SpeechSynthesizer())  
      {  
  
        // Configure the audio output.   
        synth.SetOutputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Create an XML Reader from the file, create a PromptBuilder and   
        // append the XmlReader.  
        PromptBuilder builder = new PromptBuilder();  
        builder.AppendText("4003");  
  
        // Add a handler for the SpeakProgress event.  
        synth.SpeakProgress +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeakProgressEventArgs>(synth_SpeakProgress);  
  
        // Speak the prompt and play back the output file.  
        synth.Speak(builder);  
      }  
  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Press any key to exit...");  
      Console.ReadKey();  
    }  
  
    // Write each word and its character position to the console.  
    static void synth_SpeakProgress(object sender, SpeakProgressEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speak progress -    Character position:  {0}    Text:  {1}",  
        e.CharacterPosition, e.Text);  
    }  
  }  
}  
```
